<font color="#FF0000">STOP HAVING WARS</font><br>
<tt>Sat Oct 25  9:44:56 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
The problem with war since WW1 is the technology, and the development of explosives and detonating devices that can hang around long after the fun is over. Unexploded bombs, rockets, anti-aircraft and artillery projectiles, hand grenades, torpedoes, sea mines, and land mines, are all booby traps for future generations, as we are well aware.<br><br>
I do not feel that banning or not using any one type of war device is realistic, because war in and of itself, will motivate anyone to do anything to survive. If there were a physical invasion of the United States, you bet it would be worth the risk to plant land mines to protect the country and our way of life.<br><br>
Treaties and agreements are only as worthy as the signing parties. We have but to look at history to see that most things really don't work very well in the end. Much of it is used to justify further eradication of a defeated enemy. War crimes trials are an example.<br><br>
With all this cynicism, I agree with Tom that it would be better not to have wars in the first place!  
